## Deploying to the Raspberry Pi

This project was built and tested on:

```text
Raspberry Pi 4 Model B
Raspberry Pi OS 64-bit / Debian GNU/Linux 13 "trixie"
Architecture: aarch64 / arm64
Hostname used during setup: bella-novella
Control user used during setup: bella

Wi-Fi management network: wlan0
Isolated ATA network: eth0
Pi ATA-side IP: 192.168.50.1/24
Grandstream HT812 ATA DHCP range: 192.168.50.100-192.168.50.150

FreeSWITCH install prefix: /usr/local/freeswitch
Source/build directory: /usr/local/src
FreeSWITCH runtime user/group: freeswitch:freeswitch
```

The intended topology is:

```text
Laptop / home network
        |
      Wi-Fi
        |
Raspberry Pi wlan0  = normal management network
Raspberry Pi eth0   = isolated private ATA network, 192.168.50.1/24
        |
Grandstream HT812 ATA
        |
Two analog phones:
  Line 1 = extension 101
  Line 2 = extension 102
```

FreeSWITCH should only bind SIP/RTP to the isolated Ethernet address, `192.168.50.1`. It should not expose SIP on Wi-Fi or the internet.

---

### 1. Install the OS

Use Raspberry Pi Imager and install the latest 64-bit Raspberry Pi OS.

Recommended imager settings:

```text
Hostname: bella-novella
User: bella
Enable SSH: yes
Configure Wi-Fi: yes
Wi-Fi country: US
```

After first boot, SSH into the Pi over Wi-Fi:

```sh
ssh bella@<pi-wifi-ip>
```

Confirm the OS:

```sh
uname -a
cat /etc/os-release
ip -br addr
```

Expected shape:

```text
PRETTY_NAME="Debian GNU/Linux 13 (trixie)"
Architecture: aarch64 / arm64
wlan0 UP 192.168.1.x/24
```

Update the base system:

```sh
sudo apt update
sudo apt full-upgrade -y
sudo reboot
```

