### 2. Install base build tools and utilities

```sh
sudo apt install -y \
  git curl wget ca-certificates gnupg pkg-config \
  build-essential autoconf automake libtool-bin cmake ninja-build \
  libssl-dev zlib1g-dev libpcre2-dev libedit-dev libsqlite3-dev \
  libcurl4-openssl-dev libldns-dev libspeex-dev libspeexdsp-dev \
  libopus-dev libsndfile1-dev liblua5.4-dev lua5.4 \
  libpq-dev libtiff-dev libjpeg-dev uuid-dev \
  yasm nasm python3 python3-dev python3-pip \
  dnsmasq tshark sngrep sox jq rsync
```

The Debian package version of SpanDSP may be too old for this FreeSWITCH build. On this setup, Debian provided SpanDSP `0.0.6`, while FreeSWITCH required SpanDSP `>= 3.0`, so Sofia-SIP and SpanDSP are built from source.

---

### 3. Prepare `/usr/local/src`

```sh
sudo mkdir -p /usr/local/src
sudo chown -R "$USER":"$USER" /usr/local/src
cd /usr/local/src
```

---

### 4. Build and install SpanDSP from source

```sh
cd /usr/local/src

git clone https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp.git
cd spandsp

./bootstrap.sh
./configure --prefix=/usr/local
make -j"$(nproc)"
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig
```

Verify:

```sh
pkg-config --modversion spandsp
pkg-config --cflags spandsp
pkg-config --libs spandsp
```

Expected: a modern `spandsp` version usable by FreeSWITCH, not Debian’s old `0.0.6`.

If `pkg-config` cannot find it, check:

```sh
ls /usr/local/lib/pkgconfig/spandsp.pc
echo "$PKG_CONFIG_PATH"
```

If needed:

```sh
export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/usr/local/lib/pkgconfig:${PKG_CONFIG_PATH:-}"
```

---

### 5. Build and install Sofia-SIP from source

```sh
cd /usr/local/src

git clone https://github.com/freeswitch/sofia-sip.git
cd sofia-sip

./bootstrap.sh
./configure --prefix=/usr/local
make -j"$(nproc)"
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig
```

Verify:

```sh
pkg-config --modversion sofia-sip-ua
pkg-config --cflags sofia-sip-ua
pkg-config --libs sofia-sip-ua
```

If FreeSWITCH later says it cannot find `sofia-sip-ua`, re-check `PKG_CONFIG_PATH` and run:

```sh
sudo ldconfig
```

---

### 7. Add the FreeSWITCH user and group

```sh
sudo groupadd -r freeswitch 2>/dev/null || true

sudo useradd -r \
  -g freeswitch \
  -d /usr/local/freeswitch \
  -s /usr/sbin/nologin \
  freeswitch 2>/dev/null || true

sudo chown -R freeswitch:freeswitch /usr/local/freeswitch
```

Allow FreeSWITCH to use larger file descriptor and scheduling limits:

```sh
sudo tee /etc/security/limits.d/99-freeswitch.conf >/dev/null <<'EOF'
freeswitch soft nofile 500000
freeswitch hard nofile 500000
freeswitch soft nproc 20000
freeswitch hard nproc 20000
freeswitch soft rtprio 89
freeswitch hard rtprio 89
freeswitch soft nice -10
freeswitch hard nice -10
EOF
```

Recommended sysctl tuning:

```sh
sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/99-freeswitch.conf >/dev/null <<'EOF'
fs.file-max = 1048576
net.core.somaxconn = 4096
net.ipv4.ip_local_port_range = 10000 65000
vm.swappiness = 10
vm.vfs_cache_pressure = 50
EOF

sudo sysctl --system
```

---

### 8. Put FreeSWITCH tools in the path

```sh
sudo tee /etc/profile.d/freeswitch-path.sh >/dev/null <<'EOF'
export PATH="/usr/local/freeswitch/bin:$PATH"
EOF
```

Log out/in or run:

```sh
source /etc/profile.d/freeswitch-path.sh
```

Verify:

```sh
which fs_cli
which freeswitch
```

