### 9. Configure the isolated ATA Ethernet network

The Pi’s Wi-Fi remains the management network. The Ethernet port is a private network used only for the Grandstream ATA.

Create a NetworkManager connection for `eth0`:

```sh
sudo nmcli con add type ethernet ifname eth0 con-name bella-ata-eth0 \
  connection.autoconnect yes \
  ipv4.method manual \
  ipv4.addresses 192.168.50.1/24 \
  ipv4.never-default yes \
  ipv4.ignore-auto-dns yes \
  ipv6.method disabled 2>/dev/null || true

sudo nmcli con mod bella-ata-eth0 \
  connection.interface-name eth0 \
  connection.autoconnect yes \
  ipv4.method manual \
  ipv4.addresses 192.168.50.1/24 \
  ipv4.never-default yes \
  ipv4.ignore-auto-dns yes \
  ipv6.method disabled
```

Tell NetworkManager to keep the static Ethernet IP active even if no cable is connected:

```sh
sudo mkdir -p /etc/NetworkManager/conf.d

sudo tee /etc/NetworkManager/conf.d/99-bella-eth0-ignore-carrier.conf >/dev/null <<'EOF'
[device]
match-device=interface-name:eth0
ignore-carrier=true
EOF

sudo nmcli general reload
sudo nmcli con up bella-ata-eth0 || true
```

Make sure Wi-Fi remains the default route.

List connections:

```sh
nmcli con show
```

For your Wi-Fi connection, set autoconnect and default route preference:

```sh
sudo nmcli con mod "<YOUR_WIFI_CONNECTION_NAME>" \
  connection.autoconnect yes \
  connection.autoconnect-priority 100 \
  ipv4.never-default no \
  ipv6.method auto
```

Confirm Ethernet never becomes the default route:

```sh
sudo nmcli con mod bella-ata-eth0 \
  ipv4.never-default yes \
  ipv4.ignore-auto-dns yes \
  ipv6.method disabled
```

Expected route shape:

```text
default via 192.168.1.1 dev wlan0
192.168.50.0/24 dev eth0
```

