### 10. Disable IP forwarding

This keeps the ATA-side network isolated. The Pi should not route ATA traffic out over Wi-Fi.

```sh
sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/98-bella-no-routing.conf >/dev/null <<'EOF'
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 0
net.ipv6.conf.all.forwarding = 0
EOF

sudo sysctl --system
```

Verify:

```sh
sysctl net.ipv4.ip_forward
sysctl net.ipv6.conf.all.forwarding
```

Expected:

```text
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 0
net.ipv6.conf.all.forwarding = 0
```

