### 11. Configure DHCP for the ATA

Install and configure `dnsmasq`:

```sh
sudo apt install -y dnsmasq

sudo tee /etc/dnsmasq.d/bella-ata.conf >/dev/null <<'EOF'
# Bella ATA-only DHCP scope.
# DHCP only, bound to eth0. No DNS service, no default gateway advertisement.

interface=eth0
bind-dynamic
except-interface=wlan0

port=0

dhcp-authoritative
dhcp-range=192.168.50.100,192.168.50.150,255.255.255.0,12h

# Do not advertise default gateway or DNS.
dhcp-option=3
dhcp-option=6

dhcp-option=option:domain-name,bella.local
EOF

sudo systemctl enable dnsmasq
sudo systemctl restart dnsmasq
```

Find the ATA IP after plugging it in:

```sh
cat /var/lib/misc/dnsmasq.leases
journalctl -u dnsmasq -n 100 --no-pager
ip neigh show dev eth0
```

Expected lease example:

```text
c0:74:ad:e8:ae:95 192.168.50.119
```

If the ATA web UI is only reachable from the Pi, use an SSH tunnel from your laptop:

```sh
ssh -N -L 8080:192.168.50.119:80 bella@<pi-wifi-ip>
```

Then open:

```text
http://localhost:8080
```

