### 14. Install `disco-relay`

The relay control script should be installed as:

```text
/usr/local/bin/disco-relay
```

Install it:

```sh
sudo install -m 0755 scripts/disco-relay /usr/local/bin/disco-relay
sudo chown root:root /usr/local/bin/disco-relay
```

The script controls a Waveshare 3-relay HAT using Raspberry Pi GPIOs:

```text
Relay 1 / K1: GPIO 26 / P25
Relay 2 / K2: GPIO 20 / P28
Relay 3 / K3: GPIO 21 / P29
```

Expected actuator wiring:

```text
K1 COM -> actuator terminal A
K1 NC  -> 0V
K1 NO  -> +V

K2 COM -> actuator terminal B
K2 NC  -> 0V
K2 NO  -> +V
```

Logical states:

```text
brake/default: K1 OFF, K2 OFF = A 0V, B 0V
raise/extend:  K1 ON,  K2 OFF = A +V, B 0V
lower/retract: K1 OFF, K2 ON  = A 0V, B +V
```

Test:

```sh
sudo disco-relay status
sudo disco-relay brake
sudo disco-relay raise 2 40
sudo disco-relay lower 2 60
sudo disco-relay initialize 10 0
```

Allow the `bella` user and the `freeswitch` service user to run the relay script as root without a password:

```sh
sudo tee /etc/sudoers.d/disco-relay >/dev/null <<'EOF'
bella ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/local/bin/disco-relay
freeswitch ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/local/bin/disco-relay
EOF

sudo chmod 440 /etc/sudoers.d/disco-relay
sudo visudo -c
```

In FreeSWITCH `vars.xml`, relay commands should include `/usr/bin/sudo`:

```xml
<X-PRE-PROCESS cmd="set" data="relay_brake_command=/usr/bin/sudo /usr/local/bin/disco-relay brake"/>
<X-PRE-PROCESS cmd="set" data="relay_raise_command=/usr/bin/sudo /usr/local/bin/disco-relay raise 10 40"/>
<X-PRE-PROCESS cmd="set" data="relay_lower_command=/usr/bin/sudo /usr/local/bin/disco-relay lower 10 60"/>
<X-PRE-PROCESS cmd="set" data="relay_raised_command=/usr/bin/sudo /usr/local/bin/disco-relay raised"/>
<X-PRE-PROCESS cmd="set" data="relay_lowered_command=/usr/bin/sudo /usr/local/bin/disco-relay lowered"/>
<X-PRE-PROCESS cmd="set" data="relay_status_command=/usr/bin/sudo /usr/local/bin/disco-relay status"/>
```

