### 15. Add boot-time actuator initialization

The system should start in a known safe state: fully lowered/retracted and lights/status relay off.

Create defaults:

```sh
sudo tee /etc/default/disco-relay-boot >/dev/null <<'EOF'
# Boot-time actuator initialization.
#
# Format:
#   initialize <seconds> <k3_off_after_percent>
#
# Meaning:
#   K3 OFF immediately.
#   Lower/retract for the configured time.
#   End with K1 OFF, K2 OFF, K3 OFF.

DISCO_RELAY_BOOT_COMMAND="initialize 10 0"
EOF
```

Create the service:

```sh
sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/disco-relay-boot.service >/dev/null <<'EOF'
[Unit]
Description=Initialize Disco Actuator on Boot
Documentation=file:/usr/local/bin/disco-relay
After=local-fs.target
Before=freeswitch.service
Wants=freeswitch.service

[Service]
Type=oneshot
EnvironmentFile=/etc/default/disco-relay-boot
ExecStart=/bin/bash -c '/usr/local/bin/disco-relay ${DISCO_RELAY_BOOT_COMMAND}'
TimeoutStartSec=90
RemainAfterExit=yes

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF
```

Enable it:

```sh
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable disco-relay-boot.service
sudo systemctl start disco-relay-boot.service
```

